Scenario: Online Food Ordering System
Entities

User

Restaurant

MenuItem

Order

OrderItem

Relationships

A Restaurant has many MenuItems

A User has many Orders

An Order belongs to one User

An Order has many OrderItems

An OrderItem belongs to a MenuItem

Problem Statement

Build a REST API for an Online Food Ordering System where users can browse restaurants, view menu items, and place orders.

A restaurant can list multiple food items.
A user can place multiple orders.
Each order may contain multiple food items.

The system should support creating restaurants, managing menu items, placing orders, and retrieving order details with associated data.

REST API Endpoints
Restaurant APIs
Create Restaurant
POST /restaurants

Get All Restaurants
GET /restaurants

Get Restaurant with Menu Items
GET /restaurants/:id/menu

Menu Item APIs
Add Menu Item to Restaurant
POST /restaurants/:restaurantId/menu-items

Get All Menu Items of a Restaurant
GET /restaurants/:restaurantId/menu-items

User APIs
Register User
POST /users

Get User Details
GET /users/:id

Order APIs
Place Order
POST /users/:userId/orders

Get All Orders of a User
GET /users/:userId/orders

Get Order with Order Items
GET /orders/:orderId

Advanced API (Important)
Get Order with:

User

Ordered Menu Items


This scenario will require:

hasMany

belongsTo

nested include

cascade delete

many records in one request
